=Ruy Lopez, Riga Variation, Main Line=

Black takes the hanging knight. White should reciprocate by moving [[/14. Kxh2|14. Kxh2]]. All other moves are inferior, as anything but Kxh2 or g3 will allow the bishop to get away. Moving g3 traps the bishop, but allows it to take another pawn before it dies.

{{ChessMid}}
==References==
{{reflist}}
{{wikipedia|Ruy Lopez}}

{{Chess Opening Theory/Footer}}

{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|=
|Ruy Lopez:Riga Variation|
   |rd|  |bd|kd|  |  |  |rd|=
