== Screen saver == : Sidux doesn't have any screensaver pre-installed so you can do that yourself if you want. :1. Installation: apt-get install xscreensaver xscreensaver-data xscreensaver-data-extra xscreensaver-gl xscreensaver-gl-extra :2. And run it from: Menu-> Settings-> Screensaver. ::a. Run XScreenSaver demon if the application ask for it-> OK ::b. Choose any available screensaver from the list on left side. ::c. If you want to use one screensaver choose mode: "Only One Screen Saver". ::d. If you want a screensaver to be changed automatically choose mode: "Random Screen Saver". ::e. Set time in minutes a screensaver to be blank: "Blank After". ::f. If you've chosen "Random Screen Saver" set time in minutes a screensaver to be changed: "Cycle after". ::g. If you want to stop screensavers displaying choose: "Lock Screen After". [[File:Screensaver1en.png|center|650px]] :3. In "Advanced" tab you can change some settings such as: ::a. "Display Management Enabled" - stand by, suspend and off after in minutes. ::b. "Fading and Colormaps" - fade to black when blanking, fade to black when unblanking and fade duration. [[File:Screensaver2en.png|center|650px]]
