'''Mass-analyzed ion kinetic energy spectrometry (MIKES)''' is a [[mass spectrometry]] technique by which mass spectra are obtained from a [[sector instrument]] that incorporates at least one [[magnetic]] sector plus one electric sector in reverse geometry (the beam first enters the magnetic sector).<ref name="pmid842853">{{cite journal |author=Soltero-Rigau E, Kruger TL, Cooks RG |title=Identification of barbiturates by chemical ionization and mass-analyzed ion kinetic energy spectrometry |journal=Anal. Chem. |volume=49 |issue=3 |pages=435–42 |year=1977 |pmid=842853 |doi=10.1021/ac50011a027}}</ref><ref name="pmid3356947">{{cite journal |author=Easton C, Johnson DW, Poulos A |title=Determination of phospholipid base structure by CA MIKES mass spectrometry |journal=J. Lipid Res. |volume=29 |issue=1 |pages=109–12 |year=1988 |pmid=3356947 |doi=}}</ref><ref name="pmid7242113">{{cite journal |author=Cooks RG, Kondrat RW, Youssefi M, McLaughlin JL |title=Mass-analyzed ion kinetic energy (MIKE) spectrometry and the direct analysis of coca |journal=J Ethnopharmacol |volume=3 |issue=2-3 |pages=299–312 |year=1981 |pmid=7242113 |doi=10.1016/0378-8741(81)90060-X}}</ref> The accelerating [[voltage]] ''V'', and the [[magnetic field]] ''B'', are set to select the precursor ions of a particular ''m/z''. The precursor ions then to dissociate or react in an [[electric field]]-free region between the two sectors. The ratio of the [[kinetic energy]] to charge of the product ions are analyzed by scanning the electric sector field ''E''. The width of the product ion spectrum peaks is related to the kinetic energy release distribution for the dissociation process.<ref name='Yeh 92'> {{cite journal|title=Analysis of a mass-analyzed ion kinetic energy profile. II. Systematic determination of the kinetic energy release distribution|journal=Rapid Communications in Mass Spectrometry|date=1992|first=Chul |last=Yeh|coauthors= Myung Soo Kim|volume=6|issue=4|pages=293–297|doi= 10.1002/rcm.1290060414|url=http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/cgi-bin/fulltext/110446642/PDFSTART|format=PDF|accessdate=2008-03-30 }}</ref>

